.TH "adf_sriov_configure" 9 "adf_sriov_configure" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
adf_sriov_configure \- Enable SRIOV for the device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" adf_sriov_configure
.BI "(struct pci_dev *pdev "  ","
.BI "int numvfs "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdev" 12
Pointer to PCI device.
.IP "numvfs" 12
Number of virtual functions (VFs) to enable.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Note that the \fInumvfs\fP parameter is ignored and all VFs supported by the
device are enabled due to the design of the hardware.

Function enables SRIOV for the PCI device.
.SH "RETURN"
number of VFs enabled on success, error code otherwise.
